# Database Patterns

**Reference**: See PRD.md Section 10 for complete data models and schema

## Entity Naming Conventions

### Table Names
- Use snake_case: `seats`, `check_ins`, `passengers`, `waitlist`
- Use plural form for tables
- Match entity class names (singular) to table names (plural)

### Column Names
- Use snake_case: `seat_number`, `held_until`, `created_at`
- Use descriptive names
- Avoid abbreviations unless standard (id, fk)

## JPA Entity Patterns

### Basic Entity Structure
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Proper entity structure
@Entity
@Table(name = "seats")
public class Seat {
    
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    @Column(name = "seat_id")
    private Long seatId;
    
    @Column(name = "flight_id", nullable = false)
    private String flightId;
    
    @Column(name = "seat_number", nullable = false, length = 5)
    private String seatNumber;
    
    @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
    @Column(name = "state", nullable = false)
    private SeatState state;
    
    @Version
    @Column(name = "version")
    private Integer version;
    
    @Column(name = "created_at", updatable = false)
    private LocalDateTime createdAt;
    
    @Column(name = "updated_at")
    private LocalDateTime updatedAt;
    
    // Getters, setters, constructors
}
```

### Enum Types
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Use enums for fixed states
public enum SeatState {
    AVAILABLE,
    HELD,
    CONFIRMED,
    CANCELLED
}

// In entity:
@Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
private SeatState state;
```

## Optimistic Locking

**Reference**: See PRD.md Section 5.3 for concurrency control requirements

### Version Field
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Add version field for optimistic locking
@Entity
public class Seat {
    
    @Version
    @Column(name = "version")
    private Integer version;
    
    // Other fields...
}
```

### Handling Concurrent Updates
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Handle OptimisticLockException
@Service
public class SeatServiceImpl {
    
    @Transactional
    public Seat reserveSeat(String seatId) {
        try {
            Seat seat = seatRepository.findById(seatId)
                .orElseThrow(() -> new SeatNotFoundException());
            
            if (seat.getState() != SeatState.AVAILABLE) {
                throw new SeatConflictException("Seat not available");
            }
            
            seat.setState(SeatState.HELD);
            seat.setHeldUntil(LocalDateTime.now().plusSeconds(120));
            
            return seatRepository.save(seat);
            
        } catch (OptimisticLockException e) {
            throw new SeatConflictException("Seat was modified by another transaction");
        }
    }
}
```

## State Machine Enforcement

**Reference**: See PRD.md Section 5.1 for seat state machine

### Valid State Transitions
```
AVAILABLE → HELD → CONFIRMED → CANCELLED
     ↑                            ↓
     └────────────────────────────┘
```

### Enforce in Code
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Validate state transitions
public void transitionState(SeatState newState) {
    if (!isValidTransition(this.state, newState)) {
        throw new InvalidStateTransitionException(
            String.format("Cannot transition from %s to %s", this.state, newState)
        );
    }
    this.state = newState;
}

private boolean isValidTransition(SeatState from, SeatState to) {
    switch (from) {
        case AVAILABLE:
            return to == SeatState.HELD;
        case HELD:
            return to == SeatState.CONFIRMED || to == SeatState.AVAILABLE;
        case CONFIRMED:
            return to == SeatState.CANCELLED;
        case CANCELLED:
            return to == SeatState.AVAILABLE;
        default:
            return false;
    }
}
```

## Relationships

### Many-to-One
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Proper relationship mapping
@Entity
@Table(name = "check_ins")
public class CheckIn {
    
    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
    @JoinColumn(name = "passenger_id", nullable = false)
    private Passenger passenger;
    
    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
    @JoinColumn(name = "flight_id", nullable = false)
    private Flight flight;
}
```

### One-to-Many
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Bidirectional relationship
@Entity
public class Flight {
    
    @OneToMany(mappedBy = "flight", cascade = CascadeType.ALL)
    private List<Seat> seats;
}
```

## Indexing

### Common Indexes
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Add indexes for frequently queried columns
@Entity
@Table(name = "seats", indexes = {
    @Index(name = "idx_flight_state", columnList = "flight_id, state"),
    @Index(name = "idx_held_until", columnList = "held_until")
})
public class Seat {
    // Entity fields
}
```

### Unique Constraints
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Enforce uniqueness at database level
@Entity
@Table(name = "seats", uniqueConstraints = {
    @UniqueConstraint(name = "unique_flight_seat", columnNames = {"flight_id", "seat_number"})
})
public class Seat {
    // Entity fields
}
```

## Query Patterns

### Repository Methods
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Descriptive query methods
public interface SeatRepository extends JpaRepository<Seat, Long> {
    
    List<Seat> findByFlightIdAndState(String flightId, SeatState state);
    
    Optional<Seat> findByFlightIdAndSeatNumber(String flightId, String seatNumber);
    
    @Query("SELECT s FROM Seat s WHERE s.flightId = :flightId AND s.state = 'AVAILABLE'")
    List<Seat> findAvailableSeats(@Param("flightId") String flightId);
    
    @Modifying
    @Query("UPDATE Seat s SET s.state = 'AVAILABLE' WHERE s.heldUntil < :now AND s.state = 'HELD'")
    int releaseExpiredSeats(@Param("now") LocalDateTime now);
}
```

### Avoid N+1 Queries
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Use JOIN FETCH
@Query("SELECT c FROM CheckIn c JOIN FETCH c.passenger JOIN FETCH c.seat WHERE c.checkInId = :id")
Optional<CheckIn> findByIdWithDetails(@Param("id") String id);

// ❌ BAD - Lazy loading causes N+1
CheckIn checkIn = checkInRepository.findById(id);
String passengerName = checkIn.getPassenger().getName(); // Extra query
```

## Transactions

### Transaction Boundaries
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Transaction at service layer
@Service
public class CheckInServiceImpl {
    
    @Transactional
    public CheckIn completeCheckIn(String checkInId) {
        CheckIn checkIn = checkInRepository.findById(checkInId)
            .orElseThrow(() -> new CheckInNotFoundException());
        
        Seat seat = checkIn.getSeat();
        seat.setState(SeatState.CONFIRMED);
        seatRepository.save(seat);
        
        checkIn.setStatus(CheckInStatus.COMPLETED);
        checkIn.setCompletedAt(LocalDateTime.now());
        
        return checkInRepository.save(checkIn);
    }
}
```

### Read-Only Transactions
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Mark read-only for optimization
@Transactional(readOnly = true)
public List<Seat> getAvailableSeats(String flightId) {
    return seatRepository.findByFlightIdAndState(flightId, SeatState.AVAILABLE);
}
```

## Audit Logging

### Audit Fields
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Include audit fields
@Entity
public class AuditLog {
    
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long logId;
    
    @Column(name = "entity_type", nullable = false)
    private String entityType;
    
    @Column(name = "entity_id", nullable = false)
    private String entityId;
    
    @Column(name = "action", nullable = false)
    private String action;
    
    @Column(name = "old_state", columnDefinition = "json")
    private String oldState;
    
    @Column(name = "new_state", columnDefinition = "json")
    private String newState;
    
    @Column(name = "user_id")
    private String userId;
    
    @Column(name = "timestamp", nullable = false)
    private LocalDateTime timestamp;
}
```

### Automatic Timestamps
```java
// ✅ GOOD - Use JPA lifecycle callbacks
@Entity
public class Seat {
    
    @Column(name = "created_at", updatable = false)
    private LocalDateTime createdAt;
    
    @Column(name = "updated_at")
    private LocalDateTime updatedAt;
    
    @PrePersist
    protected void onCreate() {
        createdAt = LocalDateTime.now();
        updatedAt = LocalDateTime.now();
    }
    
    @PreUpdate
    protected void onUpdate() {
        updatedAt = LocalDateTime.now();
    }
}
```

## Database Configuration

### Connection Pooling
```yaml
# application.yml
spring:
  datasource:
    hikari:
      maximum-pool-size: 20
      minimum-idle: 5
      connection-timeout: 30000
      idle-timeout: 600000
      max-lifetime: 1800000
```

### JPA Settings
```yaml
spring:
  jpa:
    hibernate:
      ddl-auto: validate  # Use 'validate' in production
    show-sql: false       # Set to true only in development
    properties:
      hibernate:
        format_sql: true
        use_sql_comments: true
```

## Performance Considerations

- Use indexes on frequently queried columns
- Implement pagination for large result sets
- Use batch operations for bulk updates
- Monitor slow queries and optimize
- Use database-level constraints for data integrity
- Implement caching for read-heavy operations (see Redis patterns)
